<title>GERMANY: Italy's Fazio says Italy &quot;ready for EMS I&quot;.</title>
<headline>Italy's Fazio says Italy &quot;ready for EMS I&quot;.</headline>
<dateline>FRANKFURT 1996-11-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Antonio Fazio, Governor of the Bank of Italy, said on Friday that Italy was ready to rejoin the European Exchange Rate Mechanism (ERM).</p>
<p>In an initial response to a question at the European Banking Congress about the lira's readiness for reentry to the ERM, which it crashed out of in 1992, Fazio said &quot;Italy is ready for EMS I.&quot;</p>
<p>Later comments made clear that Fazio was referring to the current EMS exchange rate mechanism. The governor said Italy had asked to rejoin the ERM.</p>
<p>--Frankfurt Newsroom +49 69 756525</p>
